      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay but you say \"when needed\" like there's some objective standard for that. if a country starts slapping tariffs on everything to \"protect\" its workers, isn't that just a move that fundamentally undermines the global economy and eventually makes everyone poorer? it seems like the \"safeguarding\" argument is just a way to justify bad economics. isn't the consensus basically that protectionism is a net loss?",
